paragraphs.title: Load Yelp Data challenge JSON and register as temporary view
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.sql.SparkSession
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._
import sqlContext.implicits._

val warehouseLocation = "hdfs://192.168.0.50:8020/spark-warehouse"

val spark = SparkSession
  .builder()
  .appName("Yelp academic dataset example")
  .config("spark.sql.warehouse.dir", warehouseLocation)
  .getOrCreate()

spark.sparkContext.setLogLevel("ERROR")

// Business Data frame
val business = spark.read.json("hdfs://192.168.0.50:8020/yelp-dataset/yelp_academic_dataset_business.json")

// Reviews Data frame
val reviews = spark.read.json("hdfs://192.168.0.50:8020/yelp-dataset/yelp_academic_dataset_review.json")

// Users Data frame
val users = spark.read.json("hdfs://192.168.0.50:8020/yelp-dataset/yelp_academic_dataset_user.json")

// Checkins Data frame
val checkins = spark.read.json("hdfs://192.168.0.50:8020/yelp-dataset/yelp_academic_dataset_checkin.json")

// Tips Data frame
val tips = spark.read.json("hdfs://192.168.0.50:8020/yelp-dataset/yelp_academic_dataset_tip.json")

business.createOrReplaceTempView("business")
users.createOrReplaceTempView("user")
reviews.createOrReplaceTempView("review")
checkins.createOrReplaceTempView("checkin")
tips.createOrReplaceTempView("tip")

paragraphs.title: Top 10: coolest restaurants
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT r.business_id, name, SUM(votes.cool) AS coolness
FROM review r JOIN business b
ON (r.business_id = b.business_id)
GROUP BY r.business_id, name
ORDER BY coolness DESC
LIMIT 10

paragraphs.title: Top 10 review count on specific time of year
paragraphs.text:
%sql
select name,city,categories,count(review_count) as total_count from business b join tip t on (b.business_id=t.business_id)
where date like '%7%' group by categories, city, state, name,review_count order by Total_count desc limit 10
